<p><b>Budd Schulberg</b> (March 27, 1914 – August 5, 2009) was an American <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Screenwriter" title="Screenwriter">screenwriter</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Television_producer" title="Television producer">television producer</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novelist" title="Novelist">novelist</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sports_writer" title="Sports writer" class="mw-redirect">sports writer</a>. He was known for his 1941 novel, <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/What_Makes_Sammy_Run%3F" title="What Makes Sammy Run?">What Makes Sammy Run?</a></i>, his 1947 novel <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Harder_They_Fall" title="The Harder They Fall">The Harder They Fall</a></i>, his 1954 Academy-award-winning screenplay for <i><a href="On_the_Waterfront.html" title="On the Waterfront">On the Waterfront</a></i>, and his 1957 screenplay for <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Face_in_the_Crowd_(film)" title="A Face in the Crowd (film)">A Face in the Crowd</a></i>.</p>
<p></p>
